&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Vishnu Sharma&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vishnu Sharma&lt;/strong&gt; is&amp;nbsp;the author of &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Panchatantra&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;He&amp;nbsp;was an Indian scholar.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Panchatantra refers to the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;ancient Indian collection of interrelated animal fables&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and was&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;originally written in the Sanskrit language&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It was written around&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;200 BCE&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and is one of the oldest surviving texts.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Panchatantra was translated into other languages like&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Persian, Syrian, and Arabic&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;languages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Kalidas&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;was a Sanskrit writer whose famous works include&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Abhijnanasakuntalam, Meghaduta, Raghuvamsa&lt;/span&gt;, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tulsidas&lt;/strong&gt; was known for his work&amp;nbsp;Ramcharitamanas. He was a contemporary of&amp;nbsp;William Shakespeare.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Raidas&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;was an&amp;nbsp;Indian&amp;nbsp;poet-saint&amp;nbsp;of the&amp;nbsp;Bhakti movement&amp;nbsp;during the 15th to 16th century CE. He was a poet-saint, social reformer, and spiritual figure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Adam Smith&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An Inquiry into the Nature and Causes of the Wealth of Nations&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 34); &quot;&gt;generally referred to by its shortened title&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Wealth of Nations&lt;/strong&gt;,&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 34); &quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the masterpiece&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 34); &quot;&gt;of the Scottish economist&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 34); &quot;&gt;and Adam Smith&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 34); &quot;&gt;. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 34); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 34); &quot;&gt;First published in 1776, the book offers one of the world&amp;#39;s first collected descriptions of what builds nations&amp;#39; wealth&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 34); &quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;and is today a fundamental work in classical economics.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 34); &quot;&gt;By reflecting upon the economics at the beginning of the Industrial Revolution,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 34); &quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;the book touches upon such broad topics as the division of labor, Productivity&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 34); &quot;&gt;, and the free market.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 34); &quot;&gt;Five editions of&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 34); &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Wealth of Nation&lt;/strong&gt;s&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 34); &quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;were published during Smith&amp;#39;s lifetime: in 1776, 1778,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 34); &quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;1784, 1786, and 1789.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 34); &quot;&gt;Many editions appeared after Smith&amp;#39;s death in 1790.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 34); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 34); &quot;&gt;Some important books and their authors:-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

